Inspired by this cool page, I decided to make my own Collatz Conjecture visualization. My first try looked a lot like what I saw in the Numberphile video, which was pretty good. But then I thought of trying something new by keeping the original rules and wrapping everything around a unit circle. This created 360 &quot;branches&quot;, each showing a 1-degree turn.
Even though this new approach might not reveal any groundbreaking insights into the Collatz Conjecture, I had a lot of fun with it and got some interesting results. The number 327, in particular, had a really long and cool path in this version.
